A day in the life - on set edition.

Normally I keep my personal life pretty... well... personal. But this is a banger and I've told a lot of people I am close to already. So I kinda just wanna rip the band-aid off cause it's exhausting telling people over and over again.

So, turns out I am gay! This is something I think I have known about myself for a very long time. One of my problems was I didn't know exactly what I was. It's complicated and took a long journey to process.

This has led to a lot of life change.

I don't wanna go too deep in to it. Let's just say Becca is the most amazing person on the planet and she deserves all the love in the world. We're still very close, a lot of love there. We are on our journeys in life and we all want happiness and love and that is all we can ask for.

So please spread kindness and joy and love. That's the whole point of this damned thing isn't it?

Today I am feeling very grateful, humbled... fuck I dunno... overwhelmed by the outpouring of kindness and love and support I have received in just the last 24 hrs. I really did not expect it to be like this.

Super cheeseball but in these tumultuous times I have seen the absolute best of what we have to offer on this rock from all of you. And it's just fucking awesome.

It's especially humbling to me to read the few comments from the people who maybe gained a bit of hope or greater belief in themselves from seeing my journey. I didn't expect that at all!

It doesn't matter if you are LGBQT+ or not. If you feel different, alone, estranged, confused, isolated - I'm here and I get it and I get you. Therefore - you are not alone. Do things in your own time. The water is gonna crash and go wherever it wants, but you pilot your own boat.

And a big shout out to my queer VFX friends who I know or don't know. I think VFX needs more diverse representation. The DGA just formed its first LGBQT+ committee. I challenge the VES to do the same :)
What a lovely day to be alive!
Here’s to all my trans friends and family. Past present and future!  Trans women are women. Trans men are men!
